Answer.Ans1: Yom Kippur can fall in either of the two months of Tishrei or Tishri (pronounced "tee-SH-ray"). Tishrei is the seventh month of the Hebrew calendar and is considered one of the holiest months. It is during this month that Yom Kippur, as well as other important Jewish holidays such as Rosh Hashanah, Sukkot, and Simchat Torah, are observed
Answer.Res1: The Hebrew calendar is a lunar-based calendar, which means that the months are determined by the cycles of the moon. The length of a lunar month is approximately 29.5 days, resulting in a misalignment with the solar-based Gregorian calendar, which is commonly used worldwide. To reconcile this difference and ensure that the Jewish holidays align with the appropriate seasons, the Hebrew calendar incorporates leap months periodically.
